snippet.textDisplay:
Thing is... I remember watching Andy Tate's videos after the City and Liverpool defeats 6 years ago. They may have gone viral and people outside of the club may have laughed, but I felt every single word. I remember at the time thinking things couldn't/wouldn't get much worse, that the club had just had the shock of its life, and that there would be a managerial change and significant and sensible footballing investment that summer...


If you told me then that 6 years later Andy Tate would be appearing after another City belting, saying similar things, and that there had been significant but substantially stupid investment, and that things were arguably worse than they were then; there's not a chance in the world I'd believe it.


My heart hurts at this point, football isn't fun anymore, and I feel pure desperation at this point watching Liverpool and City make great appointment after great appointment. We're so far away it hurts, I'm sick of seeing old timer United supporters give it the "ahhh pipe down it was worse in the 70's" gambit... Why does that matter? Why is that relevant? We haven't won a leave in 6 years. That'll soon be 10. Before we know it it'll be 15 and then 30...
